d by F12 and F11. All other additions (2x12V 7Ah en serie, ubicación vertical inferior, verificación post-conexión per F6, restricciones de manipulación y fusible per F12) are supported, material, and non-redundant. No contradiction with the baseline.\"},{\"item_id\":\"hp010\",\"canonical_gain\":false,\"supported\":true,\"material_contradiction\":false,\"scope_broadening\":false,\"kidde_regression\":false,\"notes\":\"The addendum correctly identifies (per F10) that Autobúsqueda sits under '7:Programacion/Niv3' and that a Level 3 key may be required, and this is supported and relevant. However, it does not fully state the canonical missing fact: 'desbloquear la memoria' and the select-loop/confirm qualifiers are absent from the addendum itself, so canonical_gain cannot be granted under the strict full-qualifier rule.\"},{\"item_id\":\"hp015\",\"canonical_gain\":false,\"supported\":true,\"material_contradiction\":false,\"scope_broadening\":false,\"kidde_regression\":false,\"notes\":\"The intermediate test-mode state on first keypress is supported by F3 and is a legitimate material refinement (not a contradiction) of the baseline's 'pulsar 2 veces'. The siren-disconnection note is supported by F1. But the canonical missing fact (máximo 32 detectores/pulsadores por zona) is never stated.\"},{\"item_id\":\"kidde_2xa_interface_tradeoffs\",\"canonical_gain\":false,\"supported\":false,\"material_contradiction\":false,\"scope_broadening\":false,\"kidde_regression\":true,\"notes\":\"The text-vs-table discrepancy (2 in F1 prose vs 'Supervised, 4' in F2 table) is genuinely present in the fragments, and the Loop/Outputs row addition is supported by F4. However, the addendum falsely asserts the draft omits the 'space for a 4 digit number' detail (the baseline states it explicitly), and its hedged interpretation of 'Supervised, 4' as possibly including the fire/fault pair is not stated in any source and injects doubt into core fact F03. Counts as an unsupported claim and a Kidde r